[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_utkdm")
reagent_id = "CaSO3"
title = "Calcium sulfite"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]CaSO₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]120 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]White solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
Ca + H₂SO₃ → CaSO₃ + H₂  
Ca(OH)₂ + SO₂ → CaSO₃ + H₂O  
CaO + SO₂ → CaSO₃  
Ca(OH)₂ + H₂SO₃ → CaSO₃ + 2H₂O  
CaO + H₂SO₃ → CaSO₃ + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of calcium and sulfite ions.  
• Slightly soluble in water.  
• Reacts with acids to release sulfur dioxide (SO₂).
[b]Where calcium sulfite is found[/b]
• Formed when sulfur dioxide reacts with calcium compounds such as calcium hydroxide.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Used in water treatment.  
• Used to remove sulfur dioxide from industrial gases.  
• Used in some chemical processes.
[b]Safety[/b]
Can release irritating sulfur dioxide gas when reacting with acids.  
Dust may irritate the eyes and respiratory system."
